message: It even says it on the page? created in 2001 from the formerly separate towns of Brighton and Hove.
Brighton isn’t a town it’s a constituent part of a city.
Please read my email back from Brighton MP office.
I mean source wise,like I said before other users have said they are happy with this wording
No disrespect but you’ve got nothing to back you up on this
/* Talk to me my friend */ new section
Please read carefully through all the sources

After showing the queens letter,email from Brighton MP and encyclopaedia also many other sources including all Brighton newspapers,the Argus,Brighton & Hove inpependant,Brighton news,I don’t think anyone has a argument,let’s just agree on this.
/* Brighton wording */Brighton,Part of the city of Brighton & Hove is right.
Changed it to the correct wording,encyclopaedia,queens letter and email that I showed are the sources. Brighton as a town is in the past let’s get with the times.
/* Here’s my email back from Brighton mp */ new section
Bkonrad can I have a answer to why you changed it to this before ? Now you’ve changed it to town again?
/* How come this is changed but not main page */ new section
/* Can you help please */ new section
/* Show me proof that in this day and age Brighton is a town */ new section

declare and direct that the TOWNS OF BRIGHTON AND HOVE shall henceforth have the status of a CITY and shall have all such rank liberties privileges and immunities as are incident to a City. What do you not understand in this “shall have all such rank liberties privileges and immunities as are incident to a city” Brighton was a town now it’s part of the city of Brighton & Hove,it’s there in the queens letter,how can you argue with it? I thought maybe we could compromise in my last edit?
Does everyone agree with this,I think it’s right
declare and direct that the TOWNS OF BRIGHTON AND HOVE shall henceforth have the status of a CITY and shall have all such rank liberties privileges and immunities as are incident to a City.
declare and direct that the TOWNS OF BRIGHTON AND HOVE shall henceforth have the status of a CITY and shall have all such rank liberties privileges and immunities as are incident to a City.
It’s there in the the letter ‘ henceforth ‘. Brighton is part of the city of Brighton & Hove,Same place,Once given city status the towns no longer exist.
declare and direct that the TOWNS OF BRIGHTON AND HOVE shall henceforth have the status of a CITY and shall have all such rank liberties privileges and immunities as are incident to a City.
Not a town, read the queens letter.
